  "prompt": "Will Northern Ireland have an independence referendum after the Brexit vote?",
  "response": "As of now, there has been no formal declaration or schedule set for an independence referendum in Northern Ireland following the Brexit vote. However, Brexit has undoubtedly reignited discussions about the future of Northern Ireland's status within the United Kingdom. Various political parties and actors have voiced differing opinions on the matter.\n\nThe Good Friday Agreement allows for a referendum on Irish reunification if it appears likely that a majority would support it. The decision to hold such a referendum lies primarily with the UK government, specifically the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, based on their assessment of public sentiment.\n\nPolitical dynamics in Northern Ireland continue to evolve, and while there is significant debate about the implications of Brexit, any move toward an independence referendum would depend on a complex interplay of political, social, and economic factors. It is a situation that requires monitoring as circumstances can change with new developments.",
